Senegalese President Abdoulaye Wade
said the West African nation will build four new universities,
including a second one in the capital, Dakar, Le Soleil
reported.  The other three will be located in rural areas in an effort
to bring university-educated professionals into  Senegal â€™s rural
governing councils, the president told students in the town of
